CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 7, 1963, pg. 19 reads: "Ladies Of Sahara - Among those who attended the recent celebration at Sahara Temple No. 2, AEA Nobles of the Mystic Shrine, were these lovely ladies of Sahara Court No. 9: First row, left to right, Eugenia Catlin, Second Ceremonial Ddt., Dts. Lois L. Dorsey, Mildred Johnson, Mary E. White, Imperial Deputy of Oasis: and Ann M. Washington, High Priestess. Back row, Dts. Mattie Blackwell, First Ceremonial Dt., Marguerite Smart, Hazel pg. Bradford, Gertrude Russell, Willa Mae Sisco, Oralee Highsmith and Mary A. Harris. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of twelve members of the Sahara Court No. 9, first row, left to right, Eugenia Catlin, Lois L. Dorsey, Mildred Johnson, Mary E. White, and Ann M. Washington, Back row, left to right, Mattie Blackwell, Marguerite Smart, Hazel P. Bradford, Gertrude Russell, Willa Mae Sisco, Oralee Highsmith and Mary A. Harris, posed on around staircase in the Sahara Temple No. 2, another version
